<title type="html"><![CDATA[In 6502 asm, how big is a &quot;word&quot;?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7767&amp;p=78378#p78378"><![CDATA[
According to the apparently and officially endorsed <a href="http://www.westerndesigncenter.com/wdc/documentation/Programmanual.pdf" class="postlink">book</a> on programming the 6502,65C02,65802 and the 65816.<br /><br />On page 13 the term "<strong>word</strong>" is not applied to 6502. You have a 8 bit <strong>byte</strong> for data items.<br /><br />For 65802 and 65816, the term <strong>double byte</strong> is used in that book.<br /><br />It also describes what <strong>word</strong> means in that PDF book.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=43">Gil-Galad</a> — Fri May 20, 2011 12:59 pm</p><hr />
